AWS offers over 400 fully featured services spanning areas like:
Compute (e.g., EC2, Lambda)
Storage (e.g., S3, EBS)
Databases (e.g., RDS, DynamoDB)
Machine Learning (e.g., SageMaker)
Networking (e.g., VPC, CloudFront)
Security, Analytics, IoT, Developer Tools, and many more.

 AWS has:
31 geographic Regions worldwide
99 Availability Zones (AZs) across these regions
What do these mean?
Regions: Independent geographic areas (like US East (N. Virginia), Asia Pacific (Mumbai), Europe (Frankfurt), etc.)
Availability Zones: Isolated data centers within a region designed for high availability and fault tolerance

★ High Availability Through Multiple Availability Zones
★ Improving Continuity With Replication Between Regions
★ Meeting Compliance and Data Residency Requirements
★ Geographic Expansion

